ategy/checkpoint_remote.go`)\\nCore logic with three functions:\\n- **`resolveCheckpointRemote(ctx, defaultRemote)`** - Entry point. Loads settings, ensures git remote, tests reachability, sets up branches. Returns `\\\"entire-checkpoints\\\"` if configured and reachable, otherwise falls back to `defaultRemote`\\n- **`ensureGitRemote(ctx, name, url)`** - Creates or updates a git remote to point to the configured URL\\n- **`isRemoteReachable(ctx, url)`** - Tests reachability via `git ls-remote --heads` with 10s timeout and `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0` to prevent interactive auth\\n- **`ensureBranchFromRemote(ctx, remote, branchName)`** - Fetches branch from remote; if it exists remotely but not locally, creates the local branch\\n\\n### PrePush (`strategy/manual_commit_push.go`)\\n- `PrePush` now calls `resolveCheckpointRemote(ctx, remote)` to determine which remote to use, then passes that to both checkpoint and trails branch pushes\\n\\n### Setup (`setup.go`)\\n- Added `CheckpointRemote` field to `EnableOptions`\\n- Added `--checkpoint-remote` flag to `entire enable`\\n- Wired into both interactive and non-interactive setup paths\\n\\n### Tests\\n- **`settings_checkpoint_remote_test.go`** - 8 tests covering: not configured, empty options, SSH URL, HTTPS URL, empty string, wrong type, JSON round-trip, coexistence with push_sessions\\n- **`checkpoint_remote_test.go`** - 10 tests covering: create/update/no-op remote, reachable/unreachable URLs, branch creation from remote, no-op when branch not on remote, resolve with no config/unreachable/reachable\\n\\n### Configuration\\nUsers configure it in `.entire/settings.json`:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"strategy_options\\\": {\\n    \\\"checkpoint_remote\\\": \\\"git@github.com:org/private-checkpoints.git\\\"\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\nOr via CLI: `entire enable --checkpoint-remote git@github.com:org/private-checkpoints.git`\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":64